CLR and NativeAOT.\n\nIn Kubernetes, I'd need to mount an `emptyDir` volume for the dumps, ensure the container has the `SYS_PTRACE` capability since `createdump` requires it to ptrace the process, and set the environment variables on the container spec.\n\nFor the dump file naming, I should use format specifiers like `%p` for PID and `%t` for timestamp to avoid collisions. Let me put together a complete pod spec YAML that shows how to configure all of this.","outputTokens":1193,"requestId":"7845:2BEA6E:1F98DAA:23186F1:69FA9D1A"},"id":"15869cfc-7f08-413b-8f0d-58b3d82b9af8","timestamp":"2026-05-06T01:47:06.763Z","parentId":"ec754251-f3d8-429a-80c0-a3ee6c64bcd5"}
