{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"1cb293f3-8718-4665-9585-b3f59223cdbb","content":"Here's what you need for automatic crash dump collection with NativeAOT:\n\n**Environment variables** configure the NativeAOT runtime to invoke `createdump` on unhandled exceptions/crashes. **`SYS_PTRACE`** is required because `createdump` uses `ptrace` to snapshot the process. An **`emptyDir` volume** gives you a writable location for dumps.\n\nAdd these to your pod spec:\n\n```yaml\nspec:\n  containers:\n    - name: your-app\n      env:\n        # Enable automatic crash dump generation\n        - name: DOTNET_DbgEnableMiniDump\n          value: \"1\"\n        # Dump type: 1=Mini, 2=Heap, 3=Triage, 4=Full\n        - name: DOTNET_DbgMiniDumpType\n          value: \"4\"\n        # Path to createdump tool (required for NativeAOT)\n        - name: DOTNET_DbgCreatedumpPath\n          value: /opt/tools/createdump\n        # Dump file path (%p=PID, %t=timestamp)\n        - name: DOTNET_DbgMiniDumpName\n          value: /tmp/dumps/coredump.%p.%t.dmp\n      securityContext:\n        capabilities:\n          add:\n            - SYS_PTRACE\n      volumeMounts:\n        - name: crash-dumps\n          mountPath: /tmp/dumps\n  volumes:\n    - name: crash-dumps\n      emptyDir:\n        sizeLimit: 2Gi\n```\n\n**Key points:**\n\n| Variable | Purpose |\n|---|---|\n| `DOTNET_DbgEnableMiniDump=1` | Enables crash dump on unhandled exception/SIGSEGV |\n| `DOTNET_DbgMiniDumpType=4` | Full dump (use `2` for heap-only to save space) |\n| `DOTNET_DbgCreatedumpPath` | Tells the NativeAOT runtime where `createdump` lives |\n| `DOTNET_DbgMiniDumpName` | Output path with `%p` (PID) and `%t` (timestamp) tokens |\n| `SYS_PTRACE` | Required — `createdump` uses `ptrace()` to read process memory |\n\n**Tip:** If you need to persist dumps beyond pod lifetime, swap the `emptyDir` for a `persistentVolumeClaim` or add a sidecar that ships dumps to blob storage.","toolRequests":[],"interactionId":"26d684cf-d00b-490f-b5c8-491bbd30cabb","reasoningOpaque":"","reasoningText":"Empty directory. Let me provide the user with the pod spec changes they need for crash dump collection with NativeAOT .NET 11.\n\nKey things needed:\n1. Environment variables for crash dump configuration\n2. `SYS_PTRACE` capability for `createdump`\n3. A volume to store dumps\n4. The `DOTNET_DbgCreatedumpPath` pointing to `/opt/tools/createdump`\n\nLet me create a YAML snippet showing the pod spec changes.","outputTokens":742,"requestId":"7840:2ED298:467F4D:51E785:69FA9D9A"},"id":"f5eef777-101d-42ba-864b-161739c6706b","timestamp":"2026-05-06T01:47:19.785Z","parentId":"067b1eca-2095-4128-8ea0-71e8585211f9"}
